<BaseLayout title="How to Write Better AI Image Prompts" description="A beginner-friendly guide to writing clearer AI image prompts." canonicalPath="/guides/how-to-write-better-prompts/"><article class="content-section article-body"><h1>How to Write Better AI Image Prompts</h1><p>Better prompts are built from specific visual choices. Start with the subject, add one action or pose, then add scene, camera, lighting, mood, style, and a few quality tags. The point is not to make the prompt huge; the point is to make every phrase useful.</p><p>Use the Builder to save fragments that work. When an image fails, change one group at a time. A prompt that says “friendly traveler standing under an umbrella, old stone street, medium wide shot, soft reflected lantern light” gives the model more structure than a pile of generic quality words.</p></article></BaseLayout>
